<img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1910/522471-625x325.jpg" alt="Creative producing for film" width="625" height="325" align="left">The workshop will be led by prominent American experts in the film industry and is open to early-to-mid-career directors and producers.The curriculum objectives are:To provide mid-career Algerian producers an overview of U.S. independent film financing strategies and explore how these practices can be applied in the Algerian context.To provide a platform for open discussion about the challenges facing producers in Algeria and how to build a sustainable career as a producer.To provide an overview of traditional and alternative distribution models, including streaming platforms.To provide participants the opportunity to workshop their pitch, discuss their projects and receive feedback from mentors and peers.